definitions.definition: The lightest and most common isotope of hydrogen , having a single proton and no neutrons : 1 H. It is the only stable nuclide with no neutrons.
examples: So far there are no differences among the protiums extracted at various labs, except for concentration levels.
This radioactive decay leaves behind a protium as well.

main_definition: ( physics ) The lightest and most common isotope of hydrogen , having a single proton and no neutrons : 1 H. It is the only stable nuclide with no neutrons.
